qas.question: Opus and Vorbis are two explans of what kind of compression format?
Being open formats means that Opus and Vorbis can be used without what?
What are some benefits to some of the newer audio compression formats when compared to MP3?

answers.text: free of some limitations inherent to the MP3 format

qas.question: How can one obtain an open compression format such as Opus or Vorbis?

context: There are also <a0_0>open<a0_0/> compression formats like Opus and Vorbis that are <a3_0>available free of charge<a3_0/> and without <a1_0>any known patent restrictions<a1_0/>. Some of the newer audio compression formats, such as AAC, WMA Pro and Vorbis, are <a2_0>free of some limitations inherent to the MP3 format<a2_0/> that cannot be overcome by any MP3 encoder.
